title: Auxbeam® How to Wire Motorcycle Auxiliary Lights - Complete Guide & Troubleshooting
description:
🔧🔧 Struggling with wiring your new motorcycle auxiliary lights? Or maybe your current lights have suddenly stopped working? This comprehensive tutorial is here to help!

In this video, I'll walk you through the complete, step-by-step process of correctly wiring your motorcycle auxiliary lights. We'll break down the function of every single wire and show you where to connect them for a safe and reliable installation. More importantly, I'll guide you through a simple troubleshooting process to diagnose and fix common issues when your lights don't turn on.

Sections:
00:02 - Understanding the Wires: What Each Color Does.
00:05 - CRUCIAL SAFETY TIP: ACC wire must be connected!
00:25 - When the wiring is correct and the ignition is on, the light behaves.
00:29 - Press the controller to test the effect.
00:46 - TROUBLESHOOTING: My Light Won't Turn On - How to Fix It!
00:49 - Case 1: ACC Wir is not connected correctly.
00:55 - Case 2: Battery Voltage is Insufficient.
01:01 - Case 3: The Controller is Broken.

Tools & Materials You Might Need:
Wire Strippers/Crimpers
Multimeter (for troubleshooting)

description:

This detailed, step-by-step tutorial is here to help! We're focusing entirely on installing the mounting brackets for the AUXBEAM 3-inch auxiliary lights on a motorcycle.

A secure bracket installation is the most important first step for adding aftermarket lights. We'll show you exactly how to find the perfect placement, align them correctly, and get them rock-solid before you even think about wiring. Get it wrong, and your lights could vibrate loose or point in the wrong direction.
